public class SinceBlockTaglet
extends ParamBlockTaglet

Since taglet implementation.

Note:

The extended since taglet supports definition of multiple since tags and can report methods with missing since tags.

Method Detail

isDefaultConstructor

protected boolean isDefaultConstructor(com.sun.javadoc.Doc tagHolder)
Check if the specified tag holder denotes a default constructor.

Note:

Default constructors are generated by the compiler, however they might not appear in the sourcecode at all. Unfortunately they are not marked as synthetic. This method does a best-effort analysis of the tag holder passed in. It is always possible to clearly state if a program element is not a default constructor, however it is not possible to distinguish an empty constructor in the source code that looks like a default constructor from a generated one.

Parameters:
tagHolder - the tag holder to analyze.
Returns:
true if the specified tag holder is probably a generated default constructor, false otherwise.
Since:
1.8.2

hasNewTag

protected boolean hasNewTag(com.sun.javadoc.Doc tagHolder)
Tests if the specified tag holder has a new tag.

New tags are used to mark a program element as "not yet released". Therefore they cannot have a since tag but we should not issue warnings for them.

Parameters:
tagHolder - the tag holder to inspect.
Returns:
true if there is a new tag attached, false otherwise.
Since:
1.9.0

configure

public void configure(Logger logger,
                      Configuration configuration)
Configures the since taglet and determines if declaration of since tags is mandatory.

Info:

Set the parameter "mandatory" to true to indicate that since tags are mandatory or false to disable since warnings. By default since warnings are not mandatory.
